  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Newly developed diagnostic parameters have potential to differentiate between epicardial
      disease and microvascular dysfunction with the help of anatomical details and physiological
      endpoints and can be used in present clinical settings.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The pressure drop coefficient (CDP) is a functional index based on hyperemic dp and u
      measurements. The lesion flow coefficient (LFC) combines the functional index CDP with an
      atomic measure (percentage area stenosis) as a single parameter.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
