  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>to detect ischemic heart disease in patients with abnormal stress tests using MPI with SPECT and to determine the presence of significant epicardial stenosis using coronary angiography with simultaneous physiological pressure and flow measurements</measure>
    <time_frame>Upon Diagnostic Angiogram and Flow Wire</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>To compare novel measurements, Pressure Drop Coefficient (CDP) &amp; Lesion Flow Coefficient (LFC), against measured current parameters called Fractional flow reserve (FFR) &amp; Coronary flow reserve (CFR).</measure>
    <time_frame>Upon Diagnostic Angiogram and Flow Wire</time_frame>
  </secondary_outcome>
